                </meridian_article_jum>
                <meridian_article_par
                    jcr:created="{Date}2026-05-12T21:44:52.810+05:30"
                    jcr:createdBy="admin"
                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-05-13T11:56:14.694+05:30"
                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="admin"
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="my-aem-site53/components/meridian-article-paragraph"
                    body="&lt;p>Santorini doesn't reveal itself all at once. The ferry rounds a black volcanic headland and suddenly the cliffs are there — chalk-white villages spilling over the caldera like sugar over the rim of a cup. I had read the warnings: too many cruise ships, too many influencers, too many sunsets photographed too many times. And yet, standing on the cobbled lip of Oia at half past seven, I forgot all of it.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                    dropCap="true"
                    textIsRich="true"/>
                <meridian_article_hea
                    jcr:created="{Date}2026-05-12T21:44:26.899+05:30"
                    jcr:createdBy="admin"
                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-05-13T11:56:36.470+05:30"
                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="admin"
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="my-aem-site53/components/meridian-article-heading"
                    anchorId="Mornings before the crowds"
                    level="h2"
                    text="Mornings before the crowds"/>
                <meridian_article_par_1378035899
                    jcr:created="{Date}2026-05-13T11:56:55.961+05:30"
                    jcr:createdBy="admin"
                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-05-13T11:57:02.628+05:30"
                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="admin"
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="my-aem-site53/components/meridian-article-paragraph"
                    body="&lt;p>The trick, as anyone who has lived on a tourist island will tell you, is to wake up before the boats do. By six the alleys belong to the bakers and the cats. I bought a bougatsa wrapped in waxed paper and ate it sitting on a low wall while the Aegean turned from slate to silver to that impossible cobalt that the postcards never quite get right.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                    dropCap="false"
                    textIsRich="true"/>
                <meridian_pull_quote
                    jcr:created="{Date}2026-05-13T11:57:45.872+05:30"
                    jcr:createdBy="admin"
                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-05-13T11:58:38.849+05:30"
                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="admin"
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="my-aem-site53/components/meridian-pull-quote"
                    quote="Some places are loved into cliché. Santorini, somehow, survives the love.&#xd;&#xa;— field notebook, day three"/>
                <meridian_article_hea_1090864520
                    jcr:created="{Date}2026-05-13T11:59:15.061+05:30"
                    jcr:createdBy="admin"
                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-05-13T11:59:24.793+05:30"
                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="admin"
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="my-aem-site53/components/meridian-article-heading"
                    anchorId="Where to actually eat"
                    level="h2"
                    text="Where to actually eat"/>
                <meridian_article_par_439656480
                    jcr:created="{Date}2026-05-13T11:59:00.786+05:30"
                    jcr:createdBy="admin"
                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-05-13T11:59:37.294+05:30"
                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="admin"
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="my-aem-site53/components/meridian-article-paragraph"
                    body="&lt;p>Skip the caldera-view restaurants with the laminated menus. Walk fifteen minutes inland and you'll find tavernas where the tomatoes taste like they were grown in a different decade — sweeter, denser, almost candied by the volcanic soil.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;"
                    dropCap="false"
                    textIsRich="true"/>
                <meridian_article_lis
                    jcr:created="{Date}2026-05-12T21:45:18.825+05:30"
                    jcr:createdBy="admin"
                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-05-13T12:00:14.404+05:30"
                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="admin"
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="my-aem-site53/components/meridian-article-list"
                    listType="unordered">
                    <items jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured">
                        <item0
                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            text="Metaxi Mas in Exo Gonia — book a week ahead, sit on the terrace."/>
                        <item1
                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            text="To Psaraki down in Vlychada for whatever was caught that morning."/>
                        <item2
                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            text="Lolita's Gelato in Oia for the salted pistachio, full stop."/>
                        <item3
                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            text="Any bakery whose front window has a tray of melitinia at 7am."/>
                    </items>
                </meridian_article_lis>
                <meridian_article_hea_1241330476
                    jcr:created="{Date}2026-05-13T12:00:27.119+05:30"
                    jcr:createdBy="admin"
                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-05-13T12:00:40.740+05:30"
                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="admin"
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="my-aem-site53/components/meridian-article-heading"
                    anchorId="A walk worth the blisters"
                    level="h2"
                    text="A walk worth the blisters"/>
                <meridian_article_par_1125813522
                    jcr:created="{Date}2026-05-13T12:00:47.001+05:30"
                    jcr:createdBy="admin"
                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-05-13T12:00:52.699+05:30"
                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="admin"
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="my-aem-site53/components/meridian-article-paragraph"
                    body="&lt;p>The cliff-top path from Fira to Oia is ten kilometres of caldera, donkey bells, and the occasional chapel painted so blue it hurts. Start before nine, carry more water than feels reasonable, and don't trust the shade.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                    dropCap="false"
                    textIsRich="true"/>
                <meridian_article_cal
                    jcr:created="{Date}2026-05-13T12:02:08.372+05:30"
                    jcr:createdBy="admin"
                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-05-13T12:03:14.250+05:30"
                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="admin"
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="my-aem-site53/components/meridian-article-callout"
                    body="&lt;p>The ferry from Athens is eight hours and beautiful for the first two. Fly in, ferry out — you'll thank yourself.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                    eyebrow="ogistics tip"
                    initial="L"
                    textIsRich="true"/>
                <meridian_article_hea_1858311141
                    jcr:created="{Date}2026-05-13T12:03:42.490+05:30"
                    jcr:createdBy="admin"
                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-05-13T12:03:49.345+05:30"
                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="admin"
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="my-aem-site53/components/meridian-article-heading"
                    anchorId="By the numbers"
                    level="h2"
                    text="By the numbers"/>
                <meridian_article_par_1828007813
                    jcr:created="{Date}2026-05-13T12:07:05.922+05:30"
                    jcr:createdBy="admin"
                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-05-13T12:07:11.678+05:30"
                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="admin"
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="my-aem-site53/components/meridian-article-paragraph"
                    body="&lt;p>I left on the late ferry, sunburnt across the bridge of my nose, my notebook smelling faintly of retsina. Santorini had been everything the brochures promised and, quietly, a great deal more.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                    dropCap="false"
                    textIsRich="true"/>
